# Google Maps API Key (optional)
# Enables precise street-level geocoding (fixes same-town location collapsing)
# AND real opening hours (the planner avoids closed days + slots visits inside
# opening hours).
#
# How to get it:
# 1. Create a Google Cloud project: https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Enable these APIs (APIs & Services → Library):
#    - Maps JavaScript API   (loads the SDK)
#    - Geocoding API          (precise coordinates)
#    - Places API (New)       (opening hours)
# 3. Create an API key: APIs & Services → Credentials
# 4. Restrict it by HTTP referrer (IMPORTANT — the key is visible client-side):
#    - Application restrictions → HTTP referrers
#    - Add: https://your-vercel-domain.vercel.app/*
#    - Add: http://localhost:*
#    - API restrictions → limit to the three APIs above
# 5. Copy the key below
#
# Leave blank to use offline coordinates (town/postal level), no opening hours.
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# Auth Redirect URLs (update with your actual domain)
# Local: http://localhost:5173
# Production: https://your-domain.com (set in Supabase console)
